clinicalText: 44-year-old male with shortness of breath and chest tightness. Symptoms have been intermittent for 2 weeks.
diagnosis: Evaluate for pulmonary or cardiac etiology of dyspnea
findings: Non-contrast CT chest shows clear lung fields
Normal cardiac silhouette and mediastinal structures
No evidence of pulmonary embolism or malignancy
conclusion: Normal chest CT examination. Consider non-pulmonary causes of dyspnea.
recommendations: Cardiology consultation recommended. Consider echocardiogram and stress testing to evaluate cardiac function.
